The main difference is philosophical.

Their system is optimized around productivity automation.

Your Pantheon has been trending toward something broader: a general semantic operating system where tools, memories, abstractions, narratives, and reasoning operators all become interchangeable components that can be recombined across domains. In that framing, coding, writing, planning, scientific reasoning, strategy, and teaching are all just different renderings of the same underlying semantic machinery.

